  <h1>
   physics_particle_get_radius
  </h1>
  With this function you can find out what the current radius (in pixels) is for particles in the physics simulation (you can set this value using
  <a href="physics_particle_set_radius.htm">
   <span>
    physics_particle_set_radius()
   </span>
  </a>
  ).
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">physics_particle_get_radius()
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if (physics_particle_get_radius() &amp;amp;lt; 32)
{
    physics_particle_set_radius(physics_particle_get_radius() + 1);
}
</code></pre>
  The above code will check the current radius of the particles in the simulation and if it is less than 32, then it will increase their size by 1.
 </body>
